name: rosB
description: rosB is part of an efflux pump/potassium antiporter system (RosAB) in Yersinia that confers resistance to cationic antimicrobial peptides such as polymyxin B.

name: rphA
description: The enzymatic inactivation of rifampin by phosphorylation at the 21-OH position.

name: rphB
description: rphB is a rifampin phosphotransferase protein found in Paenibacillus sp. LC231, a strain of Paenibacillus isolated from Lechuguilla Cave, NM, USA. Confers resistance to rifamycin antibiotics, specifically rifampin, through rifampin inactivation. Described by Pawlowski et al. 2016.

name: rpoB2
description: Due to gene duplication, the genomes of Nocardia species include both rifampin-sensitive beta-subunit of RNA polymerase (rpoB) and rifampin-resistant beta-subunit of RNA polymerase (rpoB2) genes, with ~88% similarity between the two gene products. Expression of the rpoB2 variant results in replacement of rifampin sensitivity with rifampin resistance.

name: rpsJ
description: rpsJ is a tetracycline resistance protein identified in Neisseria gonorrhoeae. Tetracycline resistance is conferred by binding to the ribosome as a 30S ribosomal protection protein.

name: RSA1-1
description: RSA1-1 is a class A beta-lactamase resistance enzyme identified from a functional metagenomic study of contaminated river sediments.

name: RSA2-1
description: RSA2-1 is a RSA2 beta-lactamase.

name: RSC1-1
description: Class C beta-lactamase RSC1-1.

name: RSD1-1
description: Class D beta-lactamase RSD1-1.

name: RSD2-1
description: RSD2-1 is a RSD2 beta-lactamase.

name: RSD2-2
description: RSD2-2 is a RSD2 beta-lactamase.

name: rsmA
description: rsmA is a gene that regulates virulence of Pseudomonas aeruginosa. However, its negative effect on MexEF-OprN overexpression has been noted to confer resistance to various antibiotics. It's Escherichia coli homolog is csrA.

name: Rhodobacter sphaeroides ampC beta-lactamase
description: A periplasmic cephalosporinase described in Rhodobacter sphaeroides shown to contribute to resistance of beta-lactam antibiotics.

name: Rv1877
description: Rv1877, a putative Major Facilitator Superfamily efflux pump from M. tuberculosis actively effluxes fluoroquinolones ofloxacin and levofloxacin.

name: putative nickel/cobalt transporter
description: Ectopic expression of NiCoT in Escherichia coli CS109 resulted in the increase of intracellular nickel uptake with enhanced tolerance towards several antibiotics when NiCoT was overexpressed in E. coli and Mycobacterium smegmatis. The presence of a sub-inhibitory dose of nickel resulted in the manifestation of low-level tolerance towards these drugs.

name: Streptococcus agalactiae mprF
description: MprF is a integral membrane protein that modifies the negatively-charged phosphatidylglycerol on the membrane surface. This confers resistance to cationic peptides that disrupt the cell membrane, including defensins.

name: salA
description: salA is an ABC-F subfamily protein gene isolated from the chromosome of Mammaliicoccus sciuri conferring resistance to lincosamides and streptogramins.

name: salB
description: salB is a ABC-F subfamily protein gene that confers resistance to lincosamides and class A streptogramins.

name: salC
description: salC is a ABC-F subfamily protein gene that confers resistance to lincosamides and class A streptogramins.

name: salD
description: salD is a ABC-F subfamily protein gene that confers resistance to lincosamides and class A streptogramins.

name: salE
description: salE is a ABC-F subfamily protein gene that confers resistance to lincosamides and class A streptogramins.

name: Streptomyces ambofaciens 23S rRNA with mutation conferring resistance to macrolide antibiotics
family_id: 23S rRNA with mutation conferring resistance to macrolide antibiotics
description: Point mutation in the 23S rRNA of Streptomyces ambofaciens shown to confer resistance to macrolide type antibiotics.

name: SAT-2
description: SAT-2 is a plasmid-mediated streptothricin acetyltransferase, which confers resistance to streptothricin, a nucleoside antibiotic. Originally described from an E. coli plasmid sequence by Heim et al., 1989.

name: SAT-3
description: SAT-3 is a plasmid-mediated streptothricin acetyltransferase and streptothricin resistance determinant. Originally described from an E. coli plasmid gene by Tietze and Brevet, 1995.

name: SAT-4
description: SAT-4 is a plasmid-mediated streptothricin acetyltransferase and streptothricin (a nucleoside antibiotic) resistant determinant. Originally described from a Campylobacter coli BE/G4 plasmid gene sequence by Jacob et al, 1994.

name: SatA
description: SatA is part of the Streptothricin acetyltransferase gene family. It confers resistance to nucleoside antibiotics.

name: Staphylococcus aureus 23S rRNA with mutation conferring resistance to linezolid
family_id: 23S rRNA with mutation conferring resistance to linezolid antibiotics
description: Point mutations in the 23S rRNA subunit of the large ribosomal bacterial subunit in Staphylococcus aureus, which confer resistance to linezolid by disrupting antibiotic target binding.

name: Staphylococcus aureus agrA with mutation conferring resistance to daptomycin
description: agrA is an autoinducer in a peptide-quorum two-component regulatory system whose mutations confer daptomycin resistance.

name: Staphylococcus aureus cls conferring resistance to daptomycin
description: Cardiolipin synthetase (cls) is an inner membrane protein that is involved in membrane synthesis. Specific mutations in S. aureus can confer resistance to daptomycin.

name: Staphylococcus aureus FosB
description: The Bacillus subtilis fosB gene encodes a fosfomycin resistance protein.

name: Staphylococcus aureus fusA with mutation conferring resistance to fusidic acid
description: The mutations to this gene are involved in altering the translation elongation factor G (EF-G) in association with the ribosome to prevent fusidic acid from binding EF-G and preventing translation.

name: Staphylococcus aureus fusE with mutation conferring resistance to fusidic acid
description: The mutations to the rplF gene encoding riboprotein L6 have been shown to cause fusidic acid resistance, demonstrating a potential secondary site of action of the antibiotic that is blocked through these mutations. Several types of mutations have been identified that cause resistance, including SNPs, frameshift mutations and early stop codons.

name: Staphylococcus aureus GlpT with mutation conferring resistance to fosfomycin
description: Mutations to the active importer GlpT, which is involved with the uptake of many phosphorylated sugars, confer resistance to fosfomycin by reducing import of the drug into the bacteria.

name: Staphylococcus aureus gyrA conferring resistance to fluoroquinolones
description: Point mutation of Staphylococcus aureus gyrA resulted in the lowered affinity between fluoroquinolones and gyrA. Thus, conferring resistance.

name: Staphylococcus aureus gyrB conferring resistance to aminocoumarin
description: Point mutation in Staphylococcus aureus resulting in aminocoumarin resistance.

name: Staphylococcus aureus ileS with mutation conferring resistance to mupirocin
description: Point mutations to the isoleucyl-tRNA synthetase (ileS) in Staphylococcus aureus that confer resistance to mupirocin.

name: Staphylococcus aureus LmrS
description: MFS transporters are secondary active transporters with single-polypeptide chains containing 400-600 amino acids that transport small solutes across the membrane by using electrochemical gradients. LmrS has 14 transmembrane helices and, when expressed in E. coli, is capable of extruding a variety of antibiotics inclinding linezolid, trimethoprim, florfenicol, chlorampheniocol, erythromycin, streptomycin, kanamycin, and fusidic acid.

name: Staphylococcus aureus menA with mutation conferring resistance to lysocin
description: menA encodes a 1,4-dihydroxy-2-naphthoate octaprenyltransferase, with mutations to the protein conferring resistance to lysocin E.

name: Staphylococcus aureus mprF
description: MprF is a integral membrane protein that modifies the negatively-charged phosphatidylglycerol on the membrane surface. A point mutation in the putative mprF synthase domain is associated with enhanced expression, increased synthesis and reduced daptomycin surface binding. This confers resistance to cationic peptides that disrupt the cell membrane, including defensins.

name: Staphylococcus aureus mprF with mutation conferring resistance to daptomycin
description: Point mutations that occur within Staphylococcus aureus mprF gene resulting in resistance to daptomycin.

name: Staphylococcus aureus mupA conferring resistance to mupirocin
description: An alternative isoleucyl-tRNA synthetase conferring resistance to mupirocin.

name: Staphylococcus aureus mupB conferring resistance to mupirocin
description: An alternative isoleucyl-tRNA synthetase conferring resistance to mupirocin.

name: Staphylococcus aureus murA with mutation conferring resistance to fosfomycin
description: murA or UDP-N-acetylglucosamine enolpyruvyl transferase catalyses the initial step in peptidoglycan biosynthesis and is inhibited by fosfomycin. Overexpression of murA through mutations confers fosfomycin resistance.

name: Staphylococcus aureus norA
description: NorA gene cloned from Staphylococcus aureus conferred relatively high resistance to hydrophilic quinolones such as norfloxacin, enoxacin, ofloxacin, and ciprofloxacin in S. aureus and Escherichia coli. Had low or no resistance at all to hydrophobic ones such as nalidixic acid, oxolinic acid, and sparfloxacin in S. aureus and Escherichia coli.

name: Staphylococcus aureus parC conferring resistance to fluoroquinolones
description: Point mutation in Staphylococcus aureus parC resulting in fluoroquinolone resistance.

name: Staphylococcus aureus parE conferring resistance to aminocoumarin
description: Point mutation in Staphylococcus aureus parE resulting in aminocoumarin resistance.

name: Staphylococcus aureus parE conferring resistance to fluoroquinolones
description: Point mutation in Staphylococcus aureus parE resulting in fluoroquinolones resistance.

name: Staphylococcus aureus pgsA mutations conferring resistance to daptomycin
description: Point mutations that occur within Staphylococcus aureus pgsA gene resulting in resistance to daptomycin.

name: Staphylococcus aureus rpoB mutants conferring resistance to daptomycin
description: Point mutations that occurs in Staphylococcus aureus rpoB resulting in resistance to daptomycin.

name: Staphylococcus aureus rpoB mutants conferring resistance to rifampicin
description: Point mutations that occurs in Staphylococcus aureus rpoB resulting in resistance to rifampicin.

name: Staphylococcus aureus rpoC conferring resistance to daptomycin
family_id: daptomycin-resistant beta prime subunit of RNA polymerase (rpoC)
description: Point mutations that occurs in Staphylococcus aureus rpoC resulting in resistance to daptomycin.

name: Staphylococcus aureus UhpT with mutation conferring resistance to fosfomycin
description: Mutations to the active importer UhpT, which is involved with the uptake of many phosphorylated sugars, confer resistance to fosfomycin by reducing import of the drug into the bacteria.

name: Staphylococcus aureus walK with mutation conferring resistance to daptomycin
description: walK is the histidine kinase sensor of a two-component regulatory system controlling peptidoglycan metabolism through regulation of the expression of most of the peptidoglycan hydrolase genes. Mutations in the gene have been found that confer daptomycin resistance.

name: sav1866
description: Sav1866 is a multidrug efflux pump in the Gram-positive Staphylococcus aureus. It is a homolog of the human ABC transporter Mdr1 and pumps out toxic compounds including verapamil, tetraphenylphosphorchloride, and Hoechst 33342.

name: Streptomyces cinnamoneus EF-Tu mutants conferring resistance to elfamycin
description: Sequence variants of Streptomyces cinnamoneus elongation factor Tu that confer resistance to elfamycin antibiotics.

name: SCO-1
description: Narrow-spectrum beta-lactamase isolated from several Acinetobacter spp. isolates from Argentina, as well as E. Coli. Hydrolyzes penicillins at a high level and cephalosporins and carbapenems at a very low level.

name: vga(E) Staphylococcus cohnii
description: vga(E) gene variant that confers resistance to pleuromutilins, lincosamides and streptogramin A antibiotics in staphylococci.

name: sdiA
description: SdiA is a cell division regulator that is also a positive regulator of AcrAB only when it's expressed from a plasmid. When the sdiA gene is on the chromosome, it has no effect on expression of acrAB.

name: sdrM
description: sdrM encodes an efflux pump that confers resistance to norfloxacin and ethidium bromide, making this a multidrug resistance gene.

name: SED-1
description: SED-1 is a chromosomal-encoded class A beta-lactamase identified in Citrobacter sedlakii.

name: SED-2
description: Class A beta-lactamase SED-2.

name: Salmonella enterica 16S rRNA (rrsD) mutation conferring resistance to spectinomycin
family_id: 16s rRNA with mutation conferring resistance to aminoglycoside antibiotics
description: Point mutations in the helix 34 region of the rrsD 16S rRNA gene of Salmonella enterica serovar Typhimurium can confer resistance to spectinomycin.

name: Salmonella enterica cmlA
description: cmlA is a plasmid-encoded chloramphenicol exporter that is found in Salmonella typhimurium.

name: Salmonella enterica gyrA conferring resistance to fluoroquinolones
description: Point mutations in Salmonella gyrA that confer resistance to Nalidixic acid, a fluoroquinolone antibiotic. These mutations have also been shown to reduce susceptibility to ciprofloxacin.

name: Salmonella enterica gyrA with mutation conferring resistance to triclosan
description: Point mutations in Salmonella enterica serovar Typhimurium which have been shown to increase the minimum inhibitory concentration of the antibiotic triclosan. It is hypothesized that decreased susceptibility to triclosan in Salmonella gyrA mutants occurs indirectly due to alterations in the stress response pathways.

name: Salmonella enterica parC conferring resistance to fluoroquinolones
description: Point mutations in Salmonella parC gene implicated in decreased susceptibility to fluoroquinolone antibiotics, primarily ciprofloxacin and nalidixic acid.

name: Salmonella enterica ramR mutants
description: RamR is a repressor that regulates RamA expression. Mutations lead to the upregulation of AcrAB, which is positively regulated by RamA.

name: Salmonella enterica soxR with mutation conferring antibiotic resistance
family_id: ATP-binding cassette (ABC) 10000 pump;major facilitator superfamily (MFS) 10000 pump;resistance-nodulation-cell division (RND) 10000 pump
description: SoxR is a sensory protein that upregulates soxS expression in the presence of redox-cycling drugs. This stress response leads to the expression of many multidrug efflux pumps.

name: Salmonella serovars soxS with mutation conferring antibiotic resistance
family_id: ATP-binding cassette (ABC) 10000 pump;General Bacterial Porin with reduced permeability to beta-lactams;major facilitator superfamily (MFS) 10000 pump;resistance-nodulation-cell division (RND) 10000 pump
description: SoxS is a global regulator that up-regulates the expression of AcrAB efflux genes. It also reduces OmpF expression to decrease cell membrane permeability.

name: sepA
description: sepA is a multidrug efflux pump that confers resistance to disinfecting agents and dyes.

name: SFB-1
description: This enzyme breaks the beta-lactam antibiotic ring open and deactivates the molecule's antibacterial properties.

name: SFC-1
description: SFC-1 is a SFC beta-lactamase.

name: SFC-2
description: Carbapenem-hydrolyzing class A beta-lactamase SFC-2.

name: SFDC-1
description: Extended-spectrum class C beta-lactamase SFDC-1.

name: SFH-1
description: SFH-1 confers resistance to carbapenems in Serratia fonticola.

name: Shigella flexneri acrA
description: AcrA is a subunit of the AcrAB multidrug efflux system found in Shigella flexneri, which is encoded by the acrRAB operon.

name: Shigella flexneri gyrA conferring resistance to fluoroquinolones
description: Point mutations in Shigella flexneri gyrA observed to confer resistance to fluoroquinolone antibiotics.

name: Shigella flexneri parC conferring resistance to fluoroquinolones
description: Point mutation in parC conferring resistance to fluoroquinolone antibiotics in Shigella flexneri,.

name: SFO-1
description: SFO-1 is a SFO beta-lactamase.

name: tlrB conferring tylosin resistance
description: TlrB is a methyltransferase found in Streptomyces fradiae and confers resistance to mycinamicin, tylosin and lincosamides. Specifically, this enzyme adds a methyl group to guanosine 748 (E. coli numbering). TlrB is found in the tylosin biosynthetic cluster and is one mechanism by which S. fradiae protects itself from self-destruction when producing this macrolide.

name: Salmonella gallinarum folP with mutation conferring resistance to sulfonamides
description: Point mutations in Salmonella gallinarum dihydropteroate synthase folP altered the stability of the protein, thus conferring sulfonamide resistance.

name: sgm
description: Sgm, or sisomicin-gentamicin methyltransferase, methylates G1405 of 16S rRNA to confer resistance to various aminoglycosides.

name: SGM-1
description: SGM-1 is a SGM beta-lactamase.

name: tet(30)
description: Tet30 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in agrobacterium, a Gram-negative bacterium.

name: tet(31)
description: Tet31 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in Aeromonas salmonicida, a Gram-negative bacteria. It has also been shown to be expressed in Gallibacterium anatis.

name: tet(32)
description: Tet(32) is a tetracycline resistance gene similar to Tet(O), and binds to the ribosome to confer tetracycline resistance as a ribosomal protection protein.

name: tet(33)
description: Tet33 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in Gram-positive bacteria, including Arthrobacter and Corynebacterium.

name: tet34
description: tet(34) causes the activation of Mg2+-dependent purine nucleotide synthesis, which protects the protein synthesis pathway. It is found in Gram-negative Vibrio.

name: tet(35)
description: Tet35 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in the Gram-negative Vibrio and Stenotrophomonas. It is unrelated to other tet resistance genes.

name: tet(36)
description: Tet(36) is a tetracycline resistance gene found in Bacteroides similar to Tet(Q), and binds to the ribosome to confer antibiotic resistance as a ribosomal protection protein.

name: tet(37)
description: tet(37) is a chromosome-encoded oxidoreductase isolated from an uncultured bacterium that confers resistance to tetracycline.

name: tet(38)
description: Tet38 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in the Gram-positive Staphylococcus aureus. It is regulated by mgrA, which also regulates NorB.

name: tet(39)
description: Tet39 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in Gram-negative bacteria, including Brevundimonas, Stenotrophomonas, Enterobacter, Alcaligenes, Acinetobacter, and Providencia.

name: tet(40)
description: Tet40 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in the Gram-positive Clostridium. It is similar to tetA(P).

name: tet(41)
description: Tet41 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in Serratia, a Gram-negative bacterium.  It is related to Acinetobacter Tet(39).

name: tet(42)
description: Tet42 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in both Gram-negative (Pseudomonas) and Gram-positive (Microbacterium, Bacillus, Staphylococcus, Paenibacillus) bacteria.

name: tet(43)
description: Tet(43) is a tetracycline resistance gene with unknown origins, isolated from metagenomic DNA.

name: tet(44)
description: Tet44 is a tetracycline resistance gene found in Campylobacter fetus, and binds to the ribosome to confer antibiotic resistance as a ribosomal protection protein.

name: tet(45)
description: Tet45 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in Bhargavaea cecembensis strain previously isolated from a poultry-litter-impacted soil.

name: tet(47)
description: A tetracycline inactivating enzyme. A flavoenzyme capable of degrading tetracycline antibiotics.

name: tet(48)
description: A tetracycline inactivating enzyme. A flavoenzyme capable of degrading tetracycline antibiotics.

name: tet(49)
description: A tetracycline inactivating enzyme. A flavoenzyme capable of degrading tetracycline antibiotics.

description: A tetracycline inactivating enzyme. A flavoenzyme capable of degrading tetracycline antibiotics.

description: A tetracycline inactivating enzyme. A flavoenzyme capable of degrading tetracycline antibiotics.

description: A tetracycline inactivating enzyme. A flavoenzyme capable of degrading tetracycline antibiotics.

name: tet(55)
description: A tetracycline inactivating enzyme. A flavoenzyme capable of degrading tetracycline antibiotics.

name: tet(56)
description: A tetracycline inactivating enzyme. A flavoenzyme capable of degrading tetracycline antibiotics.

name: tet(57)
description: A tetracycline efflux MFS Transporter from Providencia sp. Y14.

name: tet(59)
description: Tet(59) is a chromosome-encoded tetracycline efflux pump described from a Chinese pig manure sample.

name: tet(61)
description: A tetracycline-resistance ribosomal protection protein.

name: tet(62)
description: A novel tetA-type efflux pump.

name: tet(63)
description: A tetracycline efflux MFS Transporter from Staphylococcus aureus.

name: tet(64)
description: A tetracycline efflux MFS Transporter from Burkholderia ubonensis.

name: tet(65)
description: tet(65) is a tetracycline efflux gene identified from a Corynebacterium oculi plasmid.

name: tet(A)
description: TetA is a tetracycline efflux pump found in many species of Gram-negative bacteria.

name: tet(B)
description: Tet(B) is a tetracycline efflux protein expressed in many Gram-negative bacteria. It confers resistance to tetracycline, doxycycline, and minocycline, but not tigecycline.

name: tet(C)
description: Tet(C) is a tetracycline efflux pump found in many species of Gram-negative bacteria. It is typically found in plasmid DNA.

name: tet(D)
description: TetD is a tetracycline efflux pump found exclusively in Gram-negative bacteria.

name: tet(E)
description: TetE is a tetracycline efflux pump found in many Gram-negative bacteria, especially those in water environments. The gene is found on large plasmids.

name: tet(G)
description: TetG is a tetracycline efflux protein found in Gram-negative bacteria. The encoding gene is found in both chromosomal and plasmid DNA where it is frequently linked to the floR, sul1, and cmlA9 genes which encode proteins that can confer florfenicol/chloramphenicol, sulfamethoxazole, and chloramphenicol resistance, respectively.

name: tet(H)
description: TetH is a tetracycline efflux protein expressed in Gram-negative bacteria (Actinobacillus, Acinetobacter, Gallibacterium, Histophilus, Mannheimia, Moraxella, Pasteurella, and Psychrobacter). Its gene is linked to the resistance genes sul2, and strA, which confer resistance to sulfamethoxazole and streptomycin, respectively.

name: tet(J)
description: TetJ is a tetracycline efflux protein expressed in Gram-negative bacteria (Escherichia, Morganella, and Proteus).

name: tet(K)
description: TetK is a tetracycline efflux protein found in both Gram-negative (Haemophilus and Gallibacterium) and Gram-positive (many species, including mycobacteria) bacteria.

name: tet(L)
description: TetL is a tetracycline efflux protein found in many species of Gram-negative and Gram-positive bacteria.

name: tet(M)
description: Tet(M) is a ribosomal protection protein that confers tetracycline resistance. It is found on transposable DNA elements and its horizontal transfer between bacterial species has been documented.

name: tet(O)
description: Tet(O) is a ribosomal protection protein. It is associated with conjugative plasmids.

name: tet(O/32/O)
description: Tet(O/32/O) is a mosaic tetracycline resistance gene and ribosomal protection protein.

name: tet(O/M/O)
description: Tet(O/M/O) is a mosaic tetracycline resistance gene and ribosomal protection protein.

name: tet(O/W)
description: Tet(O/W) is a mosaic tetracycline resistance gene and ribosomal protection protein.

name: tet(O/W/32/O)
description: Tet(O/W/32/O) is a mosaic tetracycline resistance gene and ribosomal protection protein.

name: tet(O/W/O)
description: Tet(O/W/O) is a mosaic tetracycline resistance gene and ribosomal protection protein.

name: tet(Q)
description: Tet(Q) is a ribosomal protection protein. Its gene is associated with a conjugative transposon and has been found in both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria.

name: tet(S)
description: Tet(S) is a ribosomal protection protein found in Gram-positive and Gram-negative strains. It is similar to tet(M) and tet(O).

name: tet(T)
description: Tet(T) is a ribosomal protection protein of streptococci. It is similar to Tet(Q).

name: tet(V)
description: TetV is a tetracycline efflux protein that has been found in Mycolicibacterium smegmatis and Mycolicibacterium fortuitum.

name: tet(W)
description: Tet(W) is a ribosomal protection protein. It is associated with both conjugative and non conjugative DNA and has been found strains of Clostridioides difficile.

name: tet(W/32/O)
description: Tet(W/32/O) is a mosaic tetracycline resistance gene and ribosomal protection protein.

name: tet(W/N/W)
description: tet(W/N/W) is a mosaic tetracycline resistance gene and ribosomal protection protein.

name: tet(X)
description: Tet(X) is a flavin-dependent monooxygenase conferring resistance to tetracycline antibiotics. Tet(X) hydroxylates position 11a of the tetraketide group thus inactivating the antibiotic.

name: tet(X1)
description: Tetracycline resistance gene tet(X) ortholog described by Fang et al. 2020.

name: tet(X3)
description: A tetracyline resistance gene located on an approximately 300-kb plasmid, designated p47AB. It inactivates all tetracyclines, including tigecycline, eravacycline, and omadacycline.Adjacent to insertion sequence ISVsa3 on the conjugative plasmid.

name: tet(X4)
description: A tetracyline resistance gene located on an approximately 180-kb plasmid, designated p47EC. It inactivates all tetracyclines, including tigecycline, eravacycline, and omadacycline.Adjacent to insertion sequence ISVsa3 on the conjugative plasmid.

name: tet(X5)
description: Tet(X5) is a tetracycline inactivating enzyme. It is a variant of tet(X).

name: tet(X6)
description: Tet(X6) is a tetracycline inactivating enzyme. It is a tet(X) variant.

name: tet(Y)
description: TetY is a tetracycline efflux pump found in Gram-negative bacteria (Aeromonas and Escherichia). It is associated with plasmid DNA.

name: tet(Z)
description: TetZ is a tetracycline efflux protein found in Gram-positive bacteria (Corynebacterium and Lactobacillus). It is associated with plasmid DNA.

name: tetA(46)
description: tetA(46) is a subunit of tetAB(46), a heterodimeric ABC transporter, that is required for conferring tetracycline resistance in Streptococcus australis isolated from the oral cavity.

name: tetA(58)
description: TetA(58) is a Tetracycline efflux pump described in Paenibacillus sp. LC231, a strain of Paenibacillus isolated from Lechuguilla Cave, NM, USA. Described by Pawlowski et al. 2016.

name: tetA(60)
description: tetA(60) is a subunit of tetAB(60), an ABC transporter that confers resistance to tetracycline and tigercycline identified by screening a human saliva metagenomic library in Escherichia coli, which is required for resistance.

name: tetA(P)
description: TetA(P) is a inner membrane tetracycline efflux protein found on the same operon as the ribosomal protection protein TetB(P). It is found in Clostridium, a Gram-positive bacterium.

name: tetB(46)
description: tetB(46) is a subunit of tetAB(46), a heterodimeric ABC transporter, that is required for conferring tetracycline resistance in Streptococcus australis isolated from the oral cavity.

name: tetB(58)
description: Tetracycline resistant TetB(58) efflux pump found in Paenibacillus sp. LC231, a strain of Paenibacillus isolated from Lechuguilla Cave, NM, USA. Described by Pawlowski et al. 2016.

name: tetB(60)
description: tetB(60) is a subunit of tetAB(60), an ABC transporter that confers resistance to tetracycline and tigercycline identified by screening a human saliva metagenomic library in Escherichia coli, which is required for resistance.

name: tetB(P)
description: TetB(P) is a tetracycline ribosomal protection protein found on the same operon as tetA(P), a tetracycline efflux protein.

name: tetR
description: TetR is the repressor of the tetracycline resistance element; its N-terminal region forms a helix-turn-helix structure and binds DNA. Binding of tetracycline to TetR reduces the repressor affinity for the tetracycline resistance gene (tetA) promoter operator sites. Mutations arise within tetR results in lower affinity for tetracyclin.

name: tetR(G)
description: Class G tetracycline resistance determinant from Vibrio anguillarum.

name: ThfT
description: ThfT is an ECF transporter S component that expands the substrate profile of endogenous ECF transporters to include folate biosynthesis end products. It confers resistance to the folate synthesis inhibitor sulfamethoxazole by allowing uptake of host folate.

name: THIN-B
description: THIN-B, isolated from Janthinobacterium lividum, hydrolyzes a broad spectrum of beta-lactams including penicillins, cephalosporins, and carbapenems.

name: TLA-1
description: TLA-1 is a beta-lactamase found in plasmids of clinical isolates of Escherichia coli strain R170 in Latin America. It preferentially hydrolyzed cephaloridine, cefotaxime, cephalothin, benzylpenicillin, and ceftazidime. The enzyme was markedly inhibited by sulbactam, tazobactam, and clavulanic acid.

name: TLA-2
description: TLA-2 is a beta-lactamase is present on a plasmid isolated from an unidentified bacterial strain from a waste water treatment plant. The enzyme mostly hydrolyzes cephalosporins.

name: TLA-3
description: TLA-3 is a beta-lactamase found in a transferable plasmid of Serratia marcescens clinical isolate. It confers resistance to ceftazidime, cefotaxime and cefepime, but not to cefmetazole and meropenem.

name: tlrC
family_id: Miscellaneous ABC-F subfamily ATP-binding cassette ribosomal protection proteins
description: tlrC is an ABC-F subfamily protein found in Streptomyces fradiae and confers resistance to mycinamicin, tylosin and lincosamides. tlrC is found in the tylosin biosynthetic cluster and is one mechanism by which S. fradiae protects itself from self-destruction when producing this macrolide.

name: TMB-1
description: TMB-1 is a TMB metallo-beta-lactamase found in Achromobacter sp.

name: TMB-2
description: TMB-2 is a TMB metallo-beta-lactamase found in Acinetobacter sp.

name: tmrB
description: tmrB is an ATP-binding tunicamycin resistance protein found in Bacillus subtilis.

name: TolC
family_id: ATP-binding cassette (ABC) 10000 pump;major facilitator superfamily (MFS) 10000 pump;resistance-nodulation-cell division (RND) 10000 pump
description: TolC is a protein subunit of many multidrug efflux complexes in Gram negative bacteria. It is an outer membrane efflux protein and is constitutively open. Regulation of efflux activity is often at its periplasmic entrance by other components of the efflux complex.

name: Treponema pallidum 23S rRNA with mutation conferring resistance to erythromycin
family_id: 23S rRNA with mutation conferring resistance to macrolide antibiotics
description: Point mutations in 23S rRNA of Treponema pallidum subsp. pallidum (T. pallidum), the noncultivable agent of syphilis, shown clinically to confer resistance to erythromycin, a macrolide antibiotic.

name: TriA
description: TriA is a membrane protein that is fused to TriB and both are required for the triclosan efflux pump function of TriABC-OpmH in P. aeruginosa.

name: TriB
description: TriB is a membrane protein that is fused to TriA and both are required for the triclosan efflux pump function of TriABC-OpmH in P. aeruginosa.

name: TriC
description: TriC is a resistance nodulation cell division (RND) transporter that is a part of TriABC-OpmH, a triclosan-specific efflux protein.

name: TRU-1
description: A class C beta-lactamase enzyme identified from Aeromonas enteropelogenes. TRU-1 confers resistance to penicillin and cephalosporin antibiotics.

name: tsnR
description: tsnR is a 23S ribosomal RNA methyltransferase that methylates adenosine-1067 to confer resistance to thiostrepton.

name: Thermus thermophilus 23s rRNA conferring resistance to pleuromutilin antibiotics
family_id: 23S rRNA with mutation conferring resistance to pleuromutilin antibiotics
description: Mutations in the 23s rRNA of Thermus thermophilus confers resistance to pleuromutilin antibiotics such as tiamulin.

name: Thermus thermophilus uL3 mutations conferring resistance to pleuromutilin antibiotics
family_id: Ribosomal protein mutation conferring resistance to pleuromutilin antibiotics
description: Thermus thermophilus ribosomal protein uL3 containing various mutations conferring resistance to tiamulin. Mutations in the ribosomal protein of uL3 acts by interfering with local rRNA conformation thus conferring resistance.

name: TTU-1
description: TTU-1 is a TTU beta-lactamase.

name: TUS-1
description: TUS-1 is a chromosome-encoded beta-lactamase from Myroides odoratus and Myroides odoratimimus.

name: tva(A)
family_id: Miscellaneous ABC-F subfamily ATP-binding cassette ribosomal protection proteins
description: A pleuromutilin resistance gene encoding a predicted ABC-F transporter. The presence of inhibitory or sub-inhibitory concentrations of tiamulin showed that tva(A) confers reduced pleuromutilin susceptibility that does not lead to clinical resistance but facilitates the development of higher-level resistance via mutations in genes encoding ribosome-associated functions.

name: TxR
description: TxR is a putative transcription regulator that plays a role in conferring tetracycline resistance. It is required for proper functioning of Tet35.

name: Type A NfxB
description: Type A NfxB mutants are four to eight times more resistant to ofloxacin, erythromycin, and new zwitterionic cephems, i.e., cefpirome, cefclidin, cefozopran, and cefoselis, than the parent strain, PAO1. nfxB corresponds to 2 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 (gene name: esrC/nfxB) and 2 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58 (gene name: nfxB).

name: Type B NfxB
description: Type B NfxB mutants are more resistant to tetracycline and chloramphenicol, as well as ofloxacin, erythromycin, and the new zwitterionic cephems, than was PAO1, and they are four to eight times more susceptible to carbenicillin, sulbenicillin, imipenem, panipenem, biapenem, moxalactam, aztreonam, gentamicin, and kanamycin than PAO1. The mutation at the 46th amino acid position is sufficient for overproduction of OprJ and the multidrug resistance. nfxB corresponds to 2 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 (gene name: esrC/nfxB) and 2 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58 (gene name: nfxB).

name: ugd
description: PmrE is required for the synthesis and transfer of 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (Ara4N) to Lipid A, which allows gram-negative bacteria to resist the antimicrobial activity of cationic antimicrobial peptides and antibiotics such as polymyxin.

name: Ureaplasma urealyticum gyrB conferring resistance to fluoroquinolones
description: Point mutation in Ureaplasma urealyticum resulting in fluoroquinolone resistance.

name: Ureaplasma urealyticum parC conferring resistance to fluoroquinolones
description: Point mutation in Ureaplasma urealyticum parC resulting in fluoroquinolone resistance.

name: VAM-1
description: VAM-1 is a subclass B1 metallo-beta-lactamase, conferring resistance to beta-lactam antibiotics such as carbapenems and cephalosporins.

name: vanA
description: VanA is a D-Ala-D-Ala ligase homolog that synthesizes D-Ala-D-Lac, an alternative substrate for peptidoglycan synthesis that reduces vancomycin binding affinity. It has been isolated from VREs. It is associated with both vancomycin and teicoplanin resistance.

name: vanB
description: VanB is a D-Ala-D-Ala ligase homolog similar to VanA, and can synthesize D-Ala-D-Lac, an alternative substrate for peptidoglycan synthesis that reduces vancomycin binding affinity. It has been isolated from VREs. It is associated with vancomycin resistance, but not teicoplanin resistance.

name: vanC
description: VanC is a D-Ala-D-Ala ligase homolog that synthesizes D-Ala-D-Ser, an alternative substrate for peptidoglycan synthesis that reduces vancomycin binding affinity. It is specific to Enterococcus gallinarum and E. casseliflavus, providing intrinsic resistance.

name: vanD
description: VanD is a D-Ala-D-Ala ligase homolog similar to VanA, and can synthesize D-Ala-D-Lac, an alternative substrate for peptidoglycan synthesis that reduces vancomycin binding affinity. It is associated with both vancomycin and teicoplanin resistance.

name: vanE
description: VanE is a D-Ala-D-Ala ligase homolog that can synthesize D-Ala-D-Ser, an alternative substrate for peptidoglycan synthesis that reduces vancomycin binding affinity in Enterococcus faecalis.

name: vanF
description: VanF is a D-Ala-D-Ala ligase homolog that can synthesize D-Ala-D-Lac, an alternative substrate for peptidoglycan synthesis that reduces vancomycin binding affinity. It is associated with both vancomycin and teicoplanin resistance in Paenibacillus popilliae.

name: vanG
description: VanG is a D-Ala-D-Ala ligase homolog that can synthesize D-Ala-D-Ser, an alternative substrate for peptidoglycan synthesis that reduces vancomycin binding affinity in Enterococcus faecalis.

name: VCC-1
description: VCC-1 is a Class A carbapenemase isolated from Vibrio cholerae and exhibits resistance to penicillins, carbapenems and monobactam antibiotics.

name: Vibrio cholerae OmpT
family_id: General Bacterial Porin with reduced permeability to peptide antibiotics
description: A ToxR negatively regulated outer membrane porin. In Vibrio cholerae, ToxR controls resistance to P2 (a BPI-derived antimicrobial peptide) by regulating the production of OmpT, especially in the absence of OmpU.

name: Vibrio cholerae OmpU
family_id: General Bacterial Porin with reduced permeability to peptide antibiotics
description: A ToxR-Regulated outer membrane porin. In Vibrio cholerae, ToxR controls resistance to P2 (a BPI-derived antimicrobial peptide) by regulating the production of OmpU. OmpU also confers resistance to polymyxin B sulfate.

name: Vibrio cholerae varG
family_id: Subclass B1 Vibrio cholerae varG beta-lactamase
description: varG is an Ambler class B metallo-beta-lactamase found on the antibiotic resistance var regulon in Vibrio cholerae, along with an antibiotic efflux pump varABCDEF. These genes are organized as a regulon under the control of VarR transcriptional activator. VarG was shown to have beta-lactamase activity against penicillins, carbapenems and cephalosporins in-vitro. Described by Lin HV et al. 2017.

name: vgaA
description: vgaA is an ABC-F subfamily protein expressed in staphylococci that confers resistance to streptogramin A antibiotics and related compounds. It is associated with plasmid DNA.

name: vmlR
family_id: Miscellaneous ABC-F subfamily ATP-binding cassette ribosomal protection proteins
description: vmlR is an ABC-F ATPase ribosomal protection protein identified in Bacillus subtilus. Shown to confer resistance to lincomycin and streptogramin A virginiamycin. Described by Crowe-McAuliffe et al. 2018.

name: YojI
description: YojI mediates resistance to the peptide antibiotic microcin J25 when it is expressed from a multicopy vector. YojI is capable of pumping out microcin molecules.  The outer membrane protein TolC in addition to YojI is required for export of microcin J25 out of the cell. Microcin J25 is thus the first known substrate for YojI.

name: YRC-1
